Predictive Modeling

Problem 1: Linear Regression¶

You are hired by a company Gem Stones co ltd, which is a cubic zirconia manufacturer. You are provided with the dataset containing the prices and other attributes of almost 27,000 cubic zirconia (which is an inexpensive diamond alternative with many of the same qualities as a diamond). The company is earning different profits on different prize slots. You have to help the company in predicting the price for the stone on the bases of the details given in the dataset so it can distinguish between higher profitable stones and lower profitable stones so as to have better profit share. Also, provide them with the best 5 attributes that are most important.

Data Dictionary:¶

Variable Name - Description
Carat - Carat weight of the cubic zirconia.
Cut - Describe the cut quality of the cubic zirconia. Quality is increasing order Fair, Good, Very Good, Premium, Ideal.
Color - Colour of the cubic zirconia.With D being the worst and J the best.
Clarity - cubic zirconia Clarity refers to the absence of the Inclusions and Blemishes. (In order from Worst to Best) IF, VVS1, VVS2, VS1, VS2, Sl1, Sl2, l1
Depth - The Height of cubic zirconia, measured from the Culet to the table, divided by its average Girdle Diameter.
Table - The Width of the cubic zirconia's Table expressed as a Percentage of its Average Diameter.
Price - The Price of the cubic zirconia.
X - Length of the cubic zirconia in mm.
Y - Width of the cubic zirconia in mm.
Z - Height of the cubic zirconia in mm.

1.1. Read the data and do exploratory data analysis. Describe the data briefly. (Check the null values, Data types, shape, EDA, duplicate values). Perform Univariate and Bivariate Analysis.¶

In [38]:
def remove_outlier(col):
    sorted(col)
    Q1,Q3=col.quantile([0.25,0.75])
    IQR=Q3-Q1
    lower_range= Q1-(1.5 * IQR)
    upper_range= Q3+(1.5 * IQR)
    return lower_range, upper_range

1.4 Inference: Basis on these predictions, what are the business insights and recommendations¶

Please explain and summarise the various steps performed in this project. There should be proper business interpretation and actionable insights present.

Based on business insights, we need to summarise prediction for the company on the profits in different price slots of the stone. From the EDA analysis we can understand that as per the cut variable, ideal cut gave high profits to the company. The colours H, I, J are the best colours and gets profit for the company. In clarity, only few products are available in I1 and IF clarity stones. SI2 and I1 clarity stones gives more profit to the company. The ideal, premium and very good types of cut were bringing profits.

Predictions are captured by 95% variations in the price in the training and testing set.

Using stats model same 94% of R-squared and Adj.R-squared were predicted. As per P values and coefficients, we will be understanding the relationship. For the values more than 0.05, we can drop these variables for better results. Therefore for better accuracy we can drop the depth column.

The final Linear Regression equation is¶

b0 Intercept + b1 cut[T.2] + b2 cut[T.3] + b3 cut[T.4] + b4 color[T.2] + b5 color[T.3] + b6 color[T.4] + b7 color[T.5] + b8 color[T.6] + b9 color[T.7] + b10 clarity[T.2] + b11 clarity[T.3] + b12 clarity[T.4] + b13 clarity[T.5] + b14 clarity[T.6] + b15 clarity[T.7] + b16 clarity[T.8] + b17 carat + b18 depth + b19 table + b20 x + b21 y + b22 * z

For scaled data¶

(0.41) Intercept + (0.06) cut[T.2] + (0.09) cut[T.3] + (0.09) cut[T.4] + (-0.05) color[T.2] + (-0.07) color[T.3] + (-0.12) color[T.4] + (-0.24) color[T.5] + (-0.38) color[T.6] + (-0.54) color[T.7] + (-0.06) clarity[T.2] + (-0.07) clarity[T.3] + (-0.18) clarity[T.4] + (-0.27) clarity[T.5] + (-0.42) clarity[T.6] + (-0.66) clarity[T.7] + (-1.17) clarity[T.8] + (1.22) carat + (0.01) depth + (-0.02) table + (-0.44) x + (0.44) y + (-0.16) * z

For unscaled data¶

(859.41) Intercept + (192.44) cut[T.2] + (303.26) cut[T.3] + (321.22) cut[T.4] + (-187.69) color[T.2] + (-232.17) color[T.3] + (-412.94) color[T.4] + (-832.76) color[T.5] + (-1331.75) color[T.6] + (-1864.38) color[T.7] + (-215.17) clarity[T.2] + (-227.03) clarity[T.3] + (-636.92) clarity[T.4] + (-920.06) clarity[T.5] + (-1453.81) clarity[T.6] + (-2281.19) clarity[T.7] + (-4038.74) clarity[T.8] + (9187.94) carat + (19.17) depth + (-24.38) table + (-1363.02) x + (1372.46) y + (-803.26) * z

As per the RMSE value and coefficient of the each variable, we can use scaled data for prediction. There is also multi collinearity presence in the unscaled data.

Recommendations¶

  1. As per the insights, the ideal, premium and very good cut types are giving high profits. So, we can recommend to do marketing for these types. It also gives the better quality edge for the company and earns more profit.

  2. The clarity of the cubic zirconia is also contribute on the profit. So that needs to be focussed more on the best clarity of SI1, SI2 and I2 stones.

Important variables¶

As per the coefficients the important best 5 attributes including price are carat, Y, cut and clarity. Other variables have negative values and depth have more missing values. So, we are not going to consider depth variable. Dropping of depth will may give best accuracy.

In [142]:
def remove_outlier(col):
    sorted(col)
    Q1,Q3=col.quantile([0.25,0.75])
    IQR=Q3-Q1
    lower_range= Q1-(1.5 * IQR)
    upper_range= Q3+(1.5 * IQR)
    return lower_range, upper_range
In [143]:

    custom_prob = j #defining the cut-off value of our choice
    custom_cutoff_data=[]#defining an empty list
    for i in range(0,len(Y_train)):#defining a loop for the length of the test data
        if np.array(pred_prob_train[:,1])[i] > custom_prob:#issuing a condition for our probability values to be 
            #greater than the custom cutoff value
            a=1 #if the probability values are greater than the custom cutoff then the value should be 1
        else:
            a=0 #if the probability values are less than the custom cutoff then the value should be 0
        custom_cutoff_data.append(a)#adding either 1 or 0 based on the condition to the end of the list defined by us
    print(round(j,3),'\n')
    print('Accuracy Score',round(metrics.accuracy_score(Y_train,custom_cutoff_data),4))

2.4 Inference: Basis on these predictions, what are the insights and recommendations.¶

Please explain and summarise the various steps performed in this project. There should be proper business interpretation and actionable insights present.

We need to predict that whether an employee would opt for a holiday package or not, for this I have done predictions using both logistic regression and linear discriminant analysis. As per the prediction both results are same.

The EDA analysis clearly indicates some of below predictions. • The people aged above 50 are not interested much in holiday packages. • People from the age of 30 to 50 generally opt for holiday packages. • We can see that the employees who has salary between 20000 to 150000 always opted for Holiday package. • While considering both age and salary, in the age 30 to 50 and salary less than 50000 people have opted more for holiday package. • Employees age over 50 are not taking the holiday packages.

The important factors for the predictions are salary, age and educ.

Recommendations

  1. To improve holiday packages over the age above 50 we can provide spiritual destination places
  2. We can provide vacation holiday packages for employees who are earning more than 150000
  3. Also, we can provide packages as family holiday vacation places for employee who having more than number of older children .</p>
